Governor Yahaya Bello of Kogi State has confirmed speculation that former Minister of Aviation, Chief Femi Fani-Kayode, has joined the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC). Bello was seen addressing a crowd of APC supporters in a video on social media on Wednesday, where he confirmed that Fani-Kayode had truly joined the party as being speculated after photos of him (Bello) and Fani-Kayode went viral on Monday. READ ALSO: APC Governors’ Forum DG Warns Party Against Fani-Kayode Yahaya Bello said; “Our brother and friend, Chief Femi Fani-Kayode has joined our party in good faith. “He’s joining our party to add his own positive energy and make contributions into ensuring that APC is a party to beat.” He also reminded his audience out that Fani-Kayode was one of the foundation members of the ruling party. “Remember, Chief Femi Fani-Kayode is a foundation member of the APC,” he said.